  m_Name: Lobster
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FishData
  <fishName>k__BackingField: lobstah
  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "Lobsters are surprisingly tough survivors: they don't
    slow down or weaken with age the way most animals do, and some individuals are
    thought to live over 100 years. They taste and smell with their legs, hear with
    their bodies, and can regrow lost claws over time. Oh, and they were once so
    common in North America that they were considered poor people's food \u2014 quite
    the glow-up for today's dinner plate delicacy. "
